article_title: Doctor vacancies remain at Springfield outpatient clinic for veterans

article_metadata.description: Two of the three spots for doctors staffing a Springfield outpatient clinic for military veterans have remained unfilled for more than six months.It could be several more months before the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs has permanent replacements in place for Dinesh Doshi and Diane Bontke, who left the VA clinic in July and August, respectively.But federal officials have taken steps to get central Illinois patients served, said Diana Carranza, associate director of the VA Illiana Health
article_metadata.author: Dean Olsen Staff Writer
